label.value: negative regulation of actin cytoskeleton organization [hepatocarcinogenesis]

definition.value:
Negative regulation of actin cytoskeleton organization is a subtype of negative regulation process: A process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of actin cytoskeleton organization.
This entity is a specific course-dependent process. This process can constitute the course of hepatocarcinogenesis.
